<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-06-07T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-06-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="66" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d66">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89Belgium/44: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-06-07T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 7,
                                            1925—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>40. Your 72, June 7, 3 p.m. Department has just given to the press
                                information that Belgian Government will send mission in <pb facs="0248" n="122" xml:id="pg_122"/> July to take up debt
                                    negotiations.<note n="6" xml:id="d66fn6">The Belgian commission
                                    sailed from Cherbourg, France, on July 80. For the opening of
                                    negotiations, text of the agreement signed August 18, and other
                                    relevant material, see <hi rend="italic">Combined Annual Reports
                                        of the World War Foreign Debt Commission</hi>, pp.
                                    166–182.</note> We have also informed Morgan that Department has
                                no objection to the $50,000,000 loan.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>